    "analysis": "We have finished global aggregation of metric.csv and trace.csv (counts, min, max, mean, p50, p95) and learned available components and KPI names. Next we must detect anomalies inside the incident window (May 22, 2020 00:30 to 01:00 UTC+8) using global thresholds computed from the full series. The next atomic step is to compute per-(cmdb_id,kpi_name) global p95 and p5 thresholds (using the entire metric.csv series) and then filter metric.csv to the incident time window and find metric points that breach those thresholds (value >= p95 as high anomalies, value <= p5 as low anomalies). We should return a compact anomaly summary (counts per component, earliest anomaly timestamp per component) plus the top anomaly rows (timestamp, cmdb_id, kpi_name, value, p5, p95, anomaly_type) limited to 20 rows.",
